<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">With so many companies using up a large amount of time and resources developing data 
capturing applications, it has become evident that the various applications being developed only 
differ by their business logic i.e. the data the company is working with and the business rules 
defining the relationships between the data e.g. </span></font></div>
<div align="justify">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
<ul style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; list-style-type: disk; ">
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">PO (Purchase&nbsp; Order)</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Invoices</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">PODs (Proof Of Deliverie), </span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">GRV (Goods Received Voucher) </span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">etc. </span></font></div>
</li>
</ul>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101"><br />
</span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">The technical features/logic on the other hand mostly remain the same across every application. 
For example, every data capturing system will require:</span></font></div>
<div align="justify">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
<ul style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; list-style-type: disk; ">
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Web service</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Mobile client,</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Web Site</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Reports </span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Data Access Layer (accessing and modifying data in a database)</span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Data Transformation (i.e. XML to CSV, </span></font></div>
</li>
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Symbol;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">etc.</span></font></div>
</li>
</ul>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101"><br />
</span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Due to the business requirements varying across every project, it results in customers purchasing 
software developer hours as opposed to software products. Furthermore, this tight coupling of 
business logic with technical logic often results in the technical logic being redeveloped for every 
new project which not only results in a loss of time and resources but also inflates the 
development costs of what are often just simple data capturing applications.</span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101"><br />
</span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">The problem can solved </span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101"><br />
</span></font></div>
<div align="justify"><font face="Arial" color="#010101" size="2"><span style=" font-size:10pt; font-family:Arial; color:#010101">Figlut Suite aims to solve to this problem by is a collection applications, utilities and developer 
toolkits aimed at abstracting the technical features process of developing of data capturing 
applications. The Figlut Suite provides:</span></font></div>
<div align="justify">&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>
<ol style="margin-top: 0mm; margin-bottom: 0mm; ">
<li style="margin-left: -36pt; margin-right: 0pt; padding-left: 0pt; font-family: Arial;  font-size: 10pt;  color: #010101;  ">
